<h1><font color="red">  Student Loan <span><i></i></span> </font></h1>

<p>The Student Loan Scheme aims at providing financial support from the bank to deserving/ meritorious students for pursuing higher education in India and abroad. The main emphasis is that every meritorious student is provided with an opportunity to pursue education with the financial support on affordable terms and conditions.</p>

<h2><font color="blue"> Student'S Eligibility<span><i></i></span> </font></h2>
<p>1. Should be an Indian National</p>
<p>2. Student should have secured admission to a higher education course in recognized institutions in India or Abroad through Entrance Test/Merit based selection process after completion of HSC (10 plus 2 or equivalent).</p>
<p>3. Good academic career.</p>
<p>4. The student should not have outstanding education loan from any other Institution.</p>

<h2><font color="blue"> Expenses Considered For Loan<span><i></i></span> </font></h2>
<p>1. Fee payable to college/school/hostel</p>
<p>2. Examination/Library/Laboratory fee.</p>
<p>3. Caution deposit/building fund/refundable deposit supported by Institution bills/receipts.</p>
<p>4. Life Insurance Premium for life cover of student/co-borrower</p>

<h2><font color="blue">Quantum of Finance <span><i></i></span> </font></h2>
<p>1. Need based finance subject to earning potential of student upon completion of the course with and following ceilings</p>
<p>2. Studies in India - Maximum Rs.10.00 lakh</p>
<p>3. Studies abroad - Maximum Rs.20.00 lakh</p>


<h2><font color="blue">Margin <span><i></i></span> </font></h2>
<p>Studies in India : 7%· Scholarship could be included in margin: Margin to be brought in on year to year basis as and when disbursements are made.</p>

